title: Pac-12 basketball: Oregon State tops women's poll; Utes picked 11th
text:
San Francisco • Oregon State made a little women's basketball history here Wednesday.
For the first time, the Beavers have been picked to finish first in the Pac-12 women's basketball coaches poll. Oregon State — which returns four starters, including defensive player of the eyar Ruth Hamblin — raked in all 11 first place votes, eclipsing Stanford (2nd) and Arizona State (3rd).
Utah, under new coach Lynn Roberts, was picked to finish 11th, just ahead of last-place Arizona.
Cal and UCLA tied for fourth in the poll.
This story will be updated.
